overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application. The assistant began by
  conducting a thorough code review to understand the existing styling,
  identifying areas such as the generic color palette, plain layouts, and basic
  UI components as needing improvement. A new, calming sleep-themed color
  palette was introduced, along with custom CSS utilities for gradients and
  shadows. The main questionnaire form layout was redesigned with subtle
  background elements and an enhanced progress indicator. All core UI components
  like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards were polished with improved
  visual feedback and transitions. Consistent styling was then applied across
  all questionnaire sections, transforming generic gray boxes into cohesive,
  themed cards. During the process, a console error related to null input values
  was identified and fixed. Following initial feedback, the report section's
  inconsistent card header colors were unified to the sleep theme, and all
  remaining hardcoded gray and blue text/background colors were replaced with
  theme-based variables. The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional, and
  calming sleep questionnaire app.
